). The longitude is most likely wrong. The information available from the MNHN’s catalogue does not indicate the date of collection. Pierre Antoine Delalande (
<number box="[1271,1418,1168,1194]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="1805.0" valueMax="1823.0" valueMin="1787.0">
<date box="[1271,1418,1168,1194]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="1787" valueMax="1823">1787 – 1823</date>
</number>
), a French naturalist working for the 
<collectionCode LSID="urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" box="[562,655,1208,1234]" httpUri="http://biocol.org/urn:lsid:biocol.org:col:34988" name="Museum National d'Histoire Naturelle" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">MNHN</collectionCode>
, traveled to 
<collectingCountry box="[796,867,1208,1234]" name="Brazil" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">Brazil</collectingCountry>
in 
<number box="[904,963,1208,1234]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="1816.0">1816</number>
to collect for the Museum. He arrived in Rio de Janeiro on 
<date box="[363,448,1248,1276]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53">
June 
<number box="[424,439,1250,1276]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="1.0">1</number>
st
</date>
, and returned after a short collecting trip. So the time of collection is most likely the winter of 
<number box="[265,327,1290,1316]" pageId="2" pageNumber="53" value="1816.0">1816</number>
.
</paragraph>
